  "prompt": "How much does it cost to register a trademark in the U.S.?",
  "response": "The cost to register a trademark in the U.S. can vary based on several factors, including the filing method, the number of classes of goods or services you are registering the trademark for, and whether you are using an attorney.\n\n1. **Filing Fees**: The U.S. Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) has different filing options:\n   - **TEAS Plus**: $250 per class of goods/services (requires more upfront information).\n   - **TEAS Standard**: $350 per class of goods/services (more flexibility in terms of information but higher fee).\n\n2. **Legal Fees**: If you choose to hire a trademark attorney, legal fees can range from a few hundred to several thousand dollars depending on the complexity of the trademark and the services provided.\n\n3. **Additional Costs**: \n   - If you need to respond to any office actions or oppositions, additional legal fees may apply.\n   - Renewal fees (typically $300 per class, due every 10 years).\n\nIn summary, the basic filing fee can be as low as $250 but with legal assistance and additional services, total costs can significantly increase. It's advisable to budget anywhere from a few hundred to several thousand dollars depending on your specific needs.",
